28/09/2009
NEW YORK, United States -- During a speech Saturday (September 26th) at the UN General Assembly, Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha outlined reforms his government has undertaken on the road to EU membership. 
He cited important investments in infrastructure and the favourable business climate Albania has created. 
Berisha also described protective measures his government has launched against the global economic crisis. 
He also encouraged all UN member states to recognise Kosovo's independence from Serbia. 
(Shekulli, Top Channel, News 24 - 27/09/09; UN News Centre, B92 - 26/09/09)
